title: Nymphomaniac: Vol. I
plot: A man named Seligman finds a fainted wounded woman in an alley and he brings her home. She tells him that her name is Joe and that she is nymphomaniac. Joe tells her life and sexual experiences with hundreds of men since she was a young teenager while Seligman tells about his hobbies, such as fly fishing, reading about Fibonacci numbers or listening to organ music.
stars: Charlotte Gainsbourg, Stellan Skarsgård, Stacy Martin, Shia LaBeouf

similars.title: Antichrist
similars.plot: A grieving couple retreat to their cabin in the woods, hoping to repair their broken hearts and troubled marriage, but nature takes its course and things go from bad to worse.
similars.stars: Willem Dafoe, Charlotte Gainsbourg, Storm Acheche Sahlstrøm

similars.title: Melancholia
similars.plot: Two sisters find their already strained relationship challenged as a mysterious new planet threatens to collide with Earth.
similars.stars: Kirsten Dunst, Charlotte Gainsbourg, Kiefer Sutherland

similars.title: The House That Jack Built
similars.plot: The story follows Jack, a highly intelligent serial killer, over the course of twelve years, and depicts the murders that really develop his inner madman.
similars.stars: Matt Dillon, Bruno Ganz, Uma Thurman

similars.title: Dogville
similars.plot: A woman on the run from the mob is reluctantly accepted in a small Colorado town. In exchange, she agrees to work for them. As a search visits the town, she finds out that their support has a price. Yet her dangerous secret is never far away.
similars.stars: Nicole Kidman, Paul Bettany, Lauren Bacall

similars.title: Dancer in the Dark
similars.plot: An East European girl travels to the United States with her young son, expecting it to be like a Hollywood film.

similars.title: Breaking the Waves
similars.plot: Oilman Jan is paralyzed in an accident. His wife, who prayed for his return, feels guilty; even more, when Jan urges her to have sex with another.
similars.stars: Emily Watson, Stellan Skarsgård, Katrin Cartlidge

similars.title: Irreversible
similars.plot: Events over the course of one traumatic night in Paris unfold in reverse-chronological order as the beautiful Alex is brutally raped and beaten by a stranger in the underpass.
similars.stars: Monica Bellucci, Vincent Cassel, Albert Dupontel

similars.title: The Idiots
similars.plot: The group of people gather at the house in Copenhagen suburb to break all the limitations and to bring out the "inner idiot" in themselves.
similars.stars: Bodil Jørgensen, Jens Albinus, Anne Louise Hassing

similars.title: Manderlay
similars.plot: A story of slavery, set in the southern U.S. in the 1930s.
similars.stars: Bryce Dallas Howard, Isaach De Bankolé, Danny Glover

similars.title: The Dreamers
similars.plot: A young American studying in Paris in 1968 strikes up a friendship with a French brother and sister. Set against the background of the '68 Paris student riots.
similars.stars: Michael Pitt, Louis Garrel, Eva Green

similars.title: Love
similars.plot: Murphy is an American living in Paris who enters a highly sexually and emotionally charged relationship with the unstable Electra. Unaware of the effect it will have on their relationship, they invite their pretty neighbor into their bed.
similars.stars: Aomi Muyock, Karl Glusman, Klara Kristin

similars.title: Blue Is the Warmest Colour
similars.plot: Adèle's life is changed when she meets Emma, a young woman with blue hair, who will allow her to discover desire and to assert herself as a woman and as an adult. In front of others, Adèle grows, seeks herself, loses herself, and ultimately finds herself through love and loss.
similars.stars: Léa Seydoux, Adèle Exarchopoulos, Salim Kechiouche
